      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://nickmckay.github.io/research/paleoclimate-records/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#overview&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;anchor-symbol&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; height=&#34;26&#34; width=&#34;26&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 22 22&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76.0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71.0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71.0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76.0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We use lake sediments to develop new records of past climate. Recently, we have been developing new study areas in southern Colorado. Winter snowpack in the San Juan Mountains feed the Colorado and Rio Grande rivers, and is particularly vulnerable to rising temperatures and earlier melt seasons.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Tracing Water&#39;s Global Journey: How Temperature Has Always Driven Earth&#39;s Water Cycle</title>
      <link>https://nickmckay.github.io/blog/global-water-cycle-response/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://nickmckay.github.io/blog/global-water-cycle-response/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nickmckay.github.io/img/water-cycle-featured.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Water cycle research&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Water is life. It&amp;rsquo;s also one of the most complex and important systems on our planet. So when we ask what happens to water availability as global temperatures continue to rise, we&amp;rsquo;re really asking one of the most critical questions of our time—one with multi-billion dollar implications for societies around the world.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To find answers about the future, my colleagues and I did what paleoclimatologists do best: we looked to the past.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>actR</title>
      <link>https://nickmckay.github.io/project/actr/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Jan 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://nickmckay.github.io/project/actr/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;actR (Abrupt Change Toolkit in R) is an R package I&amp;rsquo;m developing to streamline abrupt change detection in paleoclimate datasets. This tool addresses the critical need for standardized, statistically robust methods to identify and analyze rapid climate transitions in the geological record.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;key-features&#34;&gt;Key Features&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#key-features&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;anchor-symbol&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; height=&#34;26&#34; width=&#34;26&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 22 22&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76.0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71.0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71.0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76.0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Change Detection&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>geoChronR</title>
      <link>https://nickmckay.github.io/project/geochronr/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Mar 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://nickmckay.github.io/project/geochronr/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;geoChronR is a comprehensive R package designed to help paleoscientists analyze and visualize time-uncertain data. As the lead developer, I created this tool to address the fundamental challenge of working with paleoclimate records where age models carry significant uncertainty.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;key-features&#34;&gt;Key Features&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#key-features&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;anchor-symbol&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; height=&#34;26&#34; width=&#34;26&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 22 22&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76.0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71.0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71.0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76.0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced Age Modeling&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Generate ensemble age models that capture chronological uncertainty&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Support for multiple dating methods and constraints&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Bayesian age modeling capabilities&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Time-Uncertain Analysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
